Hastings: The Department must get back on track to being a job-creator for the good of our country and economy.
Hastings: These destructive patterns that cost #jobs, block public input, and disregard #transparency must come to an end.
Hastings: The lack of #transparency has been another pattern that has emerged from the Obama Administration’s Interior Department.
Hastings: The Endangered Species Act mega-settlements are an example of closed-door agreements with litigious environmental groups.
Hastings: The Wildlands Secretarial Order and recent National Blueways Secretarial Order are examples of this Administration's overreach.
Hastings: The Obama Admin is also aggressively pursuing a #waroncoal, which is really a war on #jobs, #energy prices, & communities.
Hastings: The Obama Administration has leased the lowest number #onshore acres for #energy production in history.
Hastings: Interior has either restricted or canceled #offshore drilling plans, keeping 85% of areas off-limits.
Hastings: Under the Obama Administration, #gasprices are up and federal #energy production is down.
Hastings: Under the Obama Admin we’ve experienced 4.5 years of economically devastating policies, keeping our resources under lock-and-key
Hastings: @Interior supports millions of American #jobs and brings in the second highest source of revenue to the Treasury.
Hastings: Our resources help put Americans to work and increase our country’s economic competitiveness. #4jobs
